Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.content: ... that despite graduating last in his West Point class, Frederick Kimble eventually became a general?

entry.title: 18×2 Beyond Youthful Days (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the 2024 film 18×2 Beyond Youthful Days was filmed in Japan in March to capture both snowfalls and cherry blossoms in the same month?

entry.title: Chestnut Street Opera House (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that a will bequeathing the Chestnut Street Opera House to the University of Pennsylvania was contested at the Supreme Court of Pennsylvania?

entry.title: Jonny Pelham (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the comedian Jonny Pelham is one of an estimated 200 people in the UK to suffer from popliteal pterygium syndrome?

entry.title: You're Losing Me (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that after a CD edition of Taylor Swift's album Midnights containing the exclusive song "You're Losing Me" was released at MetLife Stadium, some of the first purchasers uploaded the song online?

entry.title: Nighat Arif (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that BBC Breakfast's resident doctor Nighat Arif has advocated for more women to be given vibrators for medical reasons?

entry.title: Soviet prisoners of war (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Soviet prisoners of war were the second-largest group of victims of Nazi mass killing?

entry.title: Katherine Sleeper Walden (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Katherine Sleeper Walden was a journalist, postmistress, innkeeper, community organizer, environmental activist, and conservationist who now has three mountains named after her?
